{{Infobox interventions | Name = Dual Therapy Stent | Image = Combo_Dual_Therapy_Stent.png | Caption = Dual therapy stent }}
A '''dual therapy stent''' is a [[coronary artery stent]] that combines the technology of a bioengineered stent and a [[drug-eluting stent|drug eluting stent]] to both accelerate healing of the vessel and to block cell proliferation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.healio.com/cardiology/intervention/news/print/cardiology-today-intervention/%7Bd6561e10-c5c0-4c9d-afbd-f65922406b27%7D/dual-therapy-stenting-the-next-step-in-the-evolution-of-stent-design|title=Dual-Therapy Stenting: The Next Step in the Evolution of Stent Design|website=www.healio.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-18}}</ref><ref>[http://www.healio.com/cardiology/intervention/news/print/cardiology-today-intervention/%7Bd6561e10-c5c0-4c9d-afbd-f65922406b27%7D/dual-therapy-stenting-the-next-step-in-the-evolution-of-stent-design Dual-Therapy Stenting: The Next Step in the Evolution of Stent Design (Cardiology Today: Intervention)]</ref>
One version combines the [[Genous]] [[endothelial progenitor cell]] capture technology with an antiproliferative, biodegradable [[sirolimus]] drug elution.<ref>London, Susan (14 November 2011). "Bioengineered, Sirolimus-Eluting Stent Found ‘Safe,’ and ‘Effective.’" Cardiology News.</ref> The Combo Stent has received [[CE Marking|CE Mark approval]].<ref>[http://www.healio.com/cardiology/intervention/news/print/cardiology-today-intervention/%7B90cdcb26-453a-4a68-8f0a-b5f457e37b3b%7D/first-dual-therapy-stent-nets-ce-mark First Dual-Therapy Stent Nets CE Mark (Cardiology Today’s Intervention)]</ref>
