{{Infobox State Senator | name =Ron Carlisle | image= | image_size=160px | caption = | state = North Dakota | state_senate =North Dakota | district = 30th | term_start = 2011 | term_end = | predecessor = | successor = | constituency = | state2 = North Dakota | state_house2=North Dakota | district2 = 30th | term_start2 =1991 | term_end2=2008 | state3 = | state_house3= | district3 = | term_start3 = | term_end3= | majority = | party = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1940|10|28}} | birth_place =[[Bismarck, North Dakota]] | death_date= | death_place = | profession =businessman | residence =Bismarck, North Dakota | relations= | alma_mater= | spouse =Neva | religion = | children= | website = |branch= |serviceyears= |rank= |battles= |allegiance= }} '''Ron D. Carlisle''' (born October 28, 1940) is an American politician in the state of [[North Dakota]]. He represents the 30th district in the [[North Dakota State Senate]]. A Republican, Carlisle was appointed to the Senate in 2011.<ref>http://votesmart.org/candidate/biography/7699/ron-carlisle#.VCyR6itdXZk</ref> He previously sat in the [[North Dakota House of Representatives]] from 1991 to his defeat in 2008. From 1976 to 2000, he was a delegate to the North Dakota State Republican Convention. He attended Bismarck State College and Black Hills State College and holds [[Bachelor of Arts]] and [[Bachelor of Science]] degrees and is a former businessman. He also served in the [[United States Navy]].<ref>https://nreca.capwiz.com/bio/id/5727&lvl=L&chamber=S</ref><ref>http://www.legis.nd.gov/assembly/63-2013/members/senate/senator-ron-carlisle</ref>
